Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.57,0:01:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Kagami.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.70,0:01:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. You're in a good mood, what's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.33,0:01:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I traded my old cell phone in for a new one!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.37,0:01:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, finally?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.04,0:01:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you can now set \Nsongs for your ringtones
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.83,0:01:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and customize your screen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.71,0:01:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already entered my favorites onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.96,0:01:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Mi-Mi-Miracle, Mikurun-run ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.68,0:01:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, that's some song you got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.82,0:02:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to pick up before it enters \Nthe chorus, so it's a shame,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or rather, don't you get stressed over it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.02,0:02:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you don't answer, it stops mid-song.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.64,0:02:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never thought about it \Nmyself, but is that how it works?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.69,0:02:13.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ring"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.69,0:02:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had to pick, Kagami is... an orc!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.89,0:02:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why am I the only monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.87,0:02:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, hello, Hiiragi here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.24,0:02:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, it's a habit from answering \Ncalls on the land-line at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.19,0:02:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was throwing her anger \Nat me until mere seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.66,0:02:34.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Today I had a sandwich that you \Npour a balsamic vinegar sauce on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.88,0:02:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can women switch gears so quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.34,0:02:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the other day, my mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.30,0:02:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have returned home!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.24,0:02:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yes, hello? Huh, Miyuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, Miyuki! Here, the phone! \NIt's from Konata-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.74,0:02:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Did I do something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.35,0:02:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Mother really is an open book,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.24,0:02:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so she's the type that you \Ncan see when she's angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, she hit her foot \Nagainst the corner of the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.45,0:03:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's a bit different \Nfrom being an open book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.41,0:03:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her personality is exactly as it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.47,0:03:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you know so much, \NMiyuki, you really help me out,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,getting me answers so quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.96,0:03:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so happy to be \Ncomplimented by my mother
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it became a habit to \Nlook up all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.79,0:03:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki, you know more than your mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.36,0:03:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's because it's \Nfun to learn something...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.68,0:03:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean I've brought you up well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.95,0:03:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the conversation we had.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.47,0:03:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that spaced-out conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, I can tell \Nyou're definitely her daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two are just alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.23,0:03:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we alike?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.29,0:03:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Completely, all the way down to the genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.11,0:03:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Miyuki, you really do \Nknow all sorts of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not just what we learn in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.61,0:03:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nowadays, there are so many \Nsources of information
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.28,0:03:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it is fun to learn \Nabout all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.33,0:03:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.12,0:03:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel up to it! I wanna play!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.42,0:03:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask others when you're in a bind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:03:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They do say that only children or \Noldest children tend to be selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you're an \Nonly child too, right, Miyuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're both only children, but I \Nguess it depends on the person, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.84,0:04:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... at home, I have an example,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.68,0:04:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or someone that seems like an older sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.82,0:04:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cleaning is a pain! Laundry exhausts me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is take-out okay for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.64,0:04:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have two older sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.69,0:04:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and all meals turn into battles for \Nfood, so you end up very tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.39,0:04:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay! Sukiyaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and eat plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.66,0:04:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, Kona-{\i1}chan {\i0}said that when \Nyour cell phone gets no reception,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's because the density of some \Nkind of particles is very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.13,0:04:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she said that when the battery is dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.41,0:04:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the situation is "Completely Silent."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.18,0:04:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids nowadays use very strange words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.77,0:04:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let's leave some for Tsukasa too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:04:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you some of my share, Tsukasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:05:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.57,0:05:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You say that, but you were \Nwolfing it down with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there are good and \Nbad things about siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.03,0:05:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only children have their \Nown problems as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.70,0:05:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}, sometimes \Nyou really space out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.46,0:05:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Space out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.91,0:05:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.59,0:05:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Considering green (horse dung) sea urchins...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.67,0:05:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they can't stand \Nthe name they've been given.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.75,0:05:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was walking while thinking, \Nand ran into the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.47,0:05:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you really concentrate so hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.00,0:05:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have lots of situations like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.60,0:05:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, how very embarrassing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.48,0:05:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, but if you start thinking \Nabout something else
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.23,0:05:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the middle of doing something, \Ndo you lack concentration skills?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.23,0:05:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, which is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.61,0:05:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That really is like you, Miyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.99,0:05:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.44,0:05:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other day, I was warming up a drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I had forgotten!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.44,0:05:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to warm it up again...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.52,0:05:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Several dozen minutes later"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.12,0:05:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... I have to do it again...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, again!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, Miyuki, you forgot again!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.38,0:06:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I couldn't help it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I have no choice. \NI'll bring it over to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.57,0:06:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.77,0:06:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And with a push!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.11,0:06:24.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Several dozen minutes later"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.07,0:06:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.32,0:06:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing less from the family \Nin the Hall of Fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is terribly embarrassing, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.48,0:06:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, when did you \Nstart wearing glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.49,0:06:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was in the last few \Nyears in elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.99,0:06:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So your eyesight wasn't \Nthat bad to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a child, I \Nreally loved all the books
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that my mother would read \Nto me before going to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But my mother would always fall asleep first,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I wanted to know how the story continued,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.60,0:06:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and tried so hard to read \Non in a dark room...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And eventually my eyesight...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.68,0:06:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's best for kids to be on \Ngood terms with their parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.22,0:06:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like in your family, Miyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:06:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that one reason why kids \Nnowadays are so indifferent and dry
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.94,0:07:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is because they lack affection, or \Nrather skinship, from their parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.11,0:07:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I wonder, when was the last time
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.19,0:07:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I got a big hug from Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, you were a spoiled child,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you were all over Mom \Nuntil about 7th grade!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.12,0:07:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that's why you're such a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.29,0:07:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my family, Dad still clings all over me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.50,0:07:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why you \Nhaven't grown up, in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.46,0:07:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of children, there \Nreally are a lot of cases
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.26,0:07:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,involving abduction or confinement \Nof young girls lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.55,0:07:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really have an eye out for \Nstuff like that for some reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.51,0:07:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But my dad's the one who \Nworries about that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say scary things like that so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.97,0:07:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure they've been \Naffected by games, more or less...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.73,0:07:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'd really like them to stop, \Nbecause it only troubles other users!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, at least, stuff like that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.98,0:07:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,never shows up in the games that I play.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right, it's almost \Nthe one-year anniversary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.62,0:07:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of me getting a part-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:08:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone at work said they \Nwould celebrate it with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.47,0:08:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I \Nhaven't been there yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll go visit you \Nwhile you work sometime,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.30,0:08:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to get back at you for New Year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.79,0:08:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, that's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.79,0:08:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine?! Isn't this usually \Nwhere people get reluctant?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.58,0:08:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, being seen is like \Nhalf of my job already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.93,0:08:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They call it a cosplay café, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.47,0:08:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Let me know in advance \Nwhen you're going to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.97,0:08:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes we're pretty busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.10,0:08:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys, class has \Nalready started, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.27,0:08:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.32,0:08:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.01,0:08:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just came out of the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, I'll get it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.58,0:08:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kona-{\i1}chan {\i0}said it was all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.37,0:08:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right, but she \Nwants me to buy this month's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.62,0:08:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,issue of Comp______ and a \NLelou__ comic over there first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will we be able to find it easily?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.46,0:08:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She reminded me to get the \Nreceipt stamped by the cashier,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's a bit confusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.11,0:08:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.85,0:09:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.10,0:09:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not Kamigishi... I'm Hiiragi...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.62,0:09:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you! What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.49,0:09:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here too for a shot, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.16,0:09:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! Stop taking pictures!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.53,0:09:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, excuse me... Can you \Nsay "Hiroyuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}" for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.49,0:09:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hiroyuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.42,0:09:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time I've \Nbeen in a store like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's so spacious that it makes you panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the phone, she told me that it \Nwould be obvious when I got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.30,0:09:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0} can figure it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.22,0:09:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'd get lost if I was by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.48,0:09:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I have to find a comic called Lelou__.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.32,0:09:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.74,0:09:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.35,0:10:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, where is the Lelou__ comic?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.24,0:10:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that would be this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.40,0:10:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Code Ge__ss...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least tell me the title so that \Nit's easy for us to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:12.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I get points on my card \Nthe next time I'm here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.09,0:10:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, please bring your card with \Nthis receipt on your next visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.09,0:10:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.48,0:10:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, all we have to do is \Ngo visit Konata's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.22,0:10:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big sister, I'm hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.76,0:10:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be getting off of work soon, \Nso hold on for a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you want us to get \Nthere, with a map like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.36,0:10:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As it so happens, I looked the \Nlocation up before coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.57,0:10:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I think it's over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.11,0:10:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing less from Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.32,0:10:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, Miyuki is the \None that we can count on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.07,0:10:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's this place, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's on the third floor of this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.71,0:10:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, my master.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.92,0:10:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.78,0:11:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first hour is 800 yen, and all \Nsoft drinks have free refills.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.97,0:11:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the games are free to play,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.06,0:11:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the sweets are all-you-can-eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.74,0:11:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I have this eel bowl?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.23,0:11:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.94,0:11:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the shrimp pilaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.11,0:11:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the meat-sauce spaghetti will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.82,0:11:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,15 minutes will be required.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your approval?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.01,0:11:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.28,0:11:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With stuff like that, can \Nthis work out as a business?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.12,0:11:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.21,0:11:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up. If you're late, \Nyou'll pay a fine, a fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.46,0:11:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the attitude you \Nshow towards your customers?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.25,0:11:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the protocol here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.13,0:11:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've decided already, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.21,0:11:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have melon soda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.01,0:11:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in an ordinary menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.83,0:11:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like a milk tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.85,0:11:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still picking one!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.43,0:11:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too slow for a brigade member.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.44,0:11:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since when am I a brigade member?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the settings for this outfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.27,0:11:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're an entire century too early \Nto disobey your brigade leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.82,0:11:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is so confusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.48,0:12:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, an iced coffee will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.36,0:12:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orders from the brigade \Nleader. Sit here and wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the first time it smelled in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.46,0:12:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna have a show on \Nstage now, so please watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.34,0:12:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ If we figured out the globe \Nlike we would a riddle ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ We could all go anywhere together ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.60,0:12:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ To the end of time, BOOON! ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.37,0:12:44.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Encore! Encore!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.86,0:12:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.15,0:12:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone performs so well!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.37,0:12:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, do the Mori version!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.79,0:12:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's an exchange student, and \Na freshman at our high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.04,0:13:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Patricia Martin. Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've released a CD, too. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:06.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mikuru"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.01,0:13:06.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Konata and Patty Cos-tte \N(Cos-it)!" "Oh My Honey"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.64,0:13:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're allowed to put \Nsomething like that on sale?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.66,0:13:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, may I have some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.39,0:13:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like it hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.39,0:13:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, please make it hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.56,0:13:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like a melon soda.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.61,0:13:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... What kind of drink \Nis this "up-to-you mix juichu"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Classified information.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Protocol, protocol!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.57,0:13:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This café is amazingly tiring...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.45,0:13:34.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nurse's Office"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.71,0:13:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My height...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.45,0:13:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.75,0:13:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you will still grow \Nmore and more in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.46,0:13:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's got to be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.72,0:13:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.38,0:13:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Yu-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.38,0:13:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I start with such a hope-destroying \Nexample right next to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.74,0:13:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, how much did you grow height-wise \Nsince you entered high school?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.44,0:14:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I haven't seen any change, \Nvertically nor horizontally.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.77,0:14:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yu-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you should be \Nprepared for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.44,0:14:06.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"touch, touch"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.57,0:14:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No depressions, don't be depressed, \Nthere is a need out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.20,0:14:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you two, have you gone to a reunion yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.83,0:14:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.45,0:14:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.96,0:14:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you asking all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The often-said "You haven't changed at all!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.09,0:14:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is usually a compliment, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.96,0:14:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the only people who \Nare happy to hear that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.84,0:14:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the ones that properly changed \Nin various places, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.76,0:14:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you cared, at least a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.02,0:14:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Golden Week is about to \Nbegin. But understand this, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.53,0:14:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from the exams you'll \Nhave right after the break,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.69,0:14:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,remember that you guys face \Nentrance exams this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.76,0:14:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and spend your break in moderation!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.69,0:14:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And furthermore,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.86,0:14:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the weekdays in-between the \Nholidays are not days off!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.28,0:14:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't authorize any plans to \Ncatch a cold and miss school!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.53,0:14:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamchatka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.70,0:14:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That aura that emanates \Nfrom the entire body...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.45,0:14:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it, it's Legendary Girl A!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.66,0:15:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that new volume today's target?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.06,0:15:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or will it be the goods?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.13,0:15:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.17,0:15:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget that we are in the \Nmiddle of the spring AV fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.01,0:15:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.04,0:15:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After drawing her in well, \Nand letting her guard down...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.72,0:15:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when we recommend something!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.73,0:15:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Wait for her to get closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.06,0:15:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.44,0:15:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Call out to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.46,0:15:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.03,0:15:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.24,0:15:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what we've recently got in stock!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.20,0:15:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kagami.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.70,0:15:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you here now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.79,0:15:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'll be right over.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.44,0:15:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was only passing time \Nwhile waiting for someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.29,0:15:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With simmering, you make rolling wedges.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.92,0:15:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You chop them into random shapes on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.09,0:15:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.05,0:15:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, you increase the surface area,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.06,0:15:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's easy for the flavor \Nto sink in, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.93,0:16:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After you skim off the scum,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.60,0:16:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,let it simmer on medium \Nheat for about ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It crumbles if you simmer it for too long,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.65,0:16:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's okay to take it off the \Nheat when a toothpick can sink in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.90,0:16:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.94,0:16:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's somewhat surprising that \Nwhen it comes to home economics,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.61,0:16:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki looks like she's below average.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I now totally understand just how \Nyou usually look at us, Kagami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.34,0:16:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiiragi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, would you \Nlike to study for the exams
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,together in the library? Think \Nof it as helping each other out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.75,0:16:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right before exams,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.92,0:16:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the usual club activities all get cancelled,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you suddenly have nothing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.46,0:16:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you study.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.42,0:16:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why there aren't any going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I understand that,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.76,0:16:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but when you're free in the times \Nthat you usually spend in your club,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.05,0:16:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you see somewhat of a \Ndifferent world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you think about that, you \Ncan't possibly study, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.60,0:16:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like you're wasting time, \Nyou get all antsy and excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.69,0:16:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, understand that half of the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.65,0:16:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why we're holding this study \Ngroup is for your sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.44,0:16:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.11,0:16:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.82,0:16:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a little break!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.61,0:16:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you can't concentrate because \Nyou don't have a goal in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.45,0:17:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have a dream of what \Nyou want to be in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.29,0:17:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dream, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.79,0:17:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like it's the future or \Nanything, but during this season,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.17,0:17:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't you just wish that you'd \Nwin the lottery or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.92,0:17:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and live an easy life? You get kinda lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.17,0:17:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minegishi, do something about that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I use my brains, sweet \Nstuff is a must after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After we get home, I'll bring you some
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.31,0:17:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the cookies I baked the other \Nday, so let's do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.64,0:17:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you bake sweets and stuff, Minegishi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.14,0:17:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, though not as much \Nas that Ajiyoshi boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.15,0:17:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, yours are more \Ndelish than Ajiyoshi's!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.15,0:17:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Studying is such a chore!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.57,0:17:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, I tried baking some madeleines!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.86,0:17:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.11,0:17:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.91,0:17:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's like birds \Nof a feather flocking together,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.99,0:17:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was just wondering whether \Nor not similar types of friends
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.49,0:17:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,naturally come together around you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.37,0:17:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you taking it lightly,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.87,0:17:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,thinking that it's just \Nanother simple canker sore?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These medical-type shows really \Nhave increased in number lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.21,0:17:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.21,0:17:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's scary because a lot of it \Nhappens really close to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, watching this \Nstuff, you start thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Maybe I'm going to die soon?" \NAnd can't stop thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It just rings too many bells.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.52,0:18:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough of negative \Nstories close to home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you, please stay alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.94,0:18:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Sis, can you teach me this part?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.95,0:18:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kazu (curses), like chickens,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.53,0:18:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,come home to roast (roost)"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.86,0:18:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.00,0:18:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazu likes chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.25,0:18:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he comes home, there is roast chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.13,0:18:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.13,0:18:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, can you translate the rest from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.44,0:18:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.88,0:18:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you make the contract...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.76,0:18:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I learn stuff like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.51,0:18:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, the other day, when I \Nwas working as a shrine maiden,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,guests from overseas were talking \Nabout the origin of the torii arch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What were they saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.86,0:18:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, it was said that \Nbirds ({\i1}tori{\i0}) carried the dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.07,0:18:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it was a tree for the birds to rest on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.15,0:19:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they call it a "bird \Nstay" (torii), apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They know more about Japan than we do!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.91,0:19:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it would have been faster \Nto just ask Kagami-{\i1}neechan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.41,0:19:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.69,0:19:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sea of Japan, where the \Nchill seeps down to the bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.54,0:19:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where has the one I love gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.30,0:19:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All alone, swimming through the \Nrough waves of show business.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.13,0:19:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have her sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Akira Kogami, with {\i1}Cape \NThirties {\i0}({\i1}Misoji Misaki{\i0})!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.51,0:19:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it! What part of this is a live show?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.97,0:19:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Considering the show's budget, \Nthis was the absolute limit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.39,0:19:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's practically Ta__ri Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.89,0:19:31.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to start!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.56,0:19:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just who do you think I am--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.10,0:19:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Can I tell a story as a monologue? ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.94,0:19:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I mumbled softly to the seagulls ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.93,0:19:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ A woman, topped with \Na one-way caring heart ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.37,0:20:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ The sea winds of the \Nnorth froze stiff ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.70,0:20:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Separated, love disperses ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.22,0:20:10.31,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It's sure taking a long time \Nfor the drinks to get here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.31,0:20:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Even words of curses ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:14.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.15,0:20:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought the drinks that you ordered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.82,0:20:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.07,0:20:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, that brown thing is {\i1}mine{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.60,0:20:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Cape Thirties ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.62,0:20:38.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"{\i1}Lucky {\i0}★{\i1} Channel {\i0}production" \N"Akira Kogami's Big Show!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.21,0:20:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.13,0:20:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Falling into tears \Nin the inn, all alone ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.35,0:20:52.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... Where is {\i1}Kentai Life Returns{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:21:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Even if I regretted \Nthe night we made love ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.65,0:21:17.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.65,0:21:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ To the splashing waves ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.00,0:21:18.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.33,0:21:19.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,An extension?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.17,0:21:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ If I were to toss them ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.17,0:21:23.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, we're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.80,0:21:25.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, my best regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.38,0:21:27.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got five minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.55,0:21:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ It seems like I can \Nsee you so far away ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.55,0:21:31.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's clean up, let's.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.26,0:21:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.44,0:21:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'd like to release a \Nsong as a solo artist, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.90,0:21:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Cape Thirties ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.90,0:21:42.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ S-S-S-Something forgotten... ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.29,0:22:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Can I tell a story as a monologue? ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.05,0:22:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I mumbled softly to the seagulls ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.25,0:22:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ A woman, topped with \Na one-way caring heart ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.65,0:22:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ The sea winds of the \Nnorth froze stiff ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.78,0:22:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Separated, love disperses ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.58,0:22:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Even words of curses ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.12,0:22:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Won't reach you so far away ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.50,0:22:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Just standing here, crying \Nuntil you're soaked ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.92,0:22:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Cape Thirties ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.32,0:23:16.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Episode Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.34,0:23:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what's with the next \Nepisode of {\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.41,0:23:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So dull. Nagato, at this \Nrate, nobody will watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.08,0:23:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to do it more like \Nsomeone cheerfully speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.63,0:23:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the TV out to the living room \Naround 6:30 PM on a Sunday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.68,0:23:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, one more time. Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.96,0:23:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what's with the next \Nepisode of {\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.26,0:23:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't change! Oh, I don't care anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.14,0:23:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode: Base of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.35,0:23:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.52,0:23:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, rock, paper, scissors!
